The aim of the course is to learn the theoretical basics of interpretation (consecutive, simultaneous, sight translation, community interpreting). Lectures are accompanied by practical seminars, where students can practice all listed interpretation types.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course teaches the main types of interpretation and the basics of memory and note-taking techniques. Students practice listening and analyzing speeches of different lengths and levels of difficulty and composing different types of speeches (argumentative, descriptive, etc.). The course provides an opportunity to test yourself in the role of an interpreter in different situations and to practice the main interpreting techniques (consecutive interpreting, simultaneous interpreting, sight interpreting).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has completed the course is able  - to distinguish and describe the main types of interpretation; - to apply the learned memory, note-taking and interpreting techniques in an interpreting situation; - to demonstrate the ability to actively listen to and analyze texts of different lengths and levels of difficulty; - to compose different types of speeches.
